WEBVTT

00:01.043 --> 00:03.420
ECHOING VOICE:
What is the fu-- What is the fu--

00:03.420 --> 00:05.255
♪ What is the future... ♪

00:05.255 --> 00:07.508
♪ What is the fu-- What is the fu-- ♪

00:07.508 --> 00:09.134
♪ What is the future? ♪

00:09.134 --> 00:12.137
♪ theme song playing ♪

00:12.137 --> 00:13.889
♪ What is the future... ♪

00:37.079 --> 00:40.249
♪

00:40.249 --> 00:42.417
- News! Bad!

00:42.417 --> 00:43.669
We're bankrupt.

00:43.669 --> 00:47.381
Oh, I borrowed money to invest in Bitcoin.

00:47.381 --> 00:50.759
Then the price crashed,
and I sold at a huge loss.

00:50.759 --> 00:52.219
We're ruined!

00:52.219 --> 00:55.848
Oh, sorry. I didn't realize
you were watching TV.

00:55.848 --> 00:59.351
- The tragic impact
destroyed the planet Klarg,

00:59.351 --> 01:02.271
along with its 50 billion inhabitants.

01:02.271 --> 01:03.647
[laughs]

01:03.647 --> 01:06.149
- In other news, Morbo, guess what's back?

01:06.149 --> 01:08.026
- The planet Klarg?
- Nope!

01:08.026 --> 01:09.778
The price of Bitcoin!

01:09.778 --> 01:10.863
- Uh, wha?!

01:10.863 --> 01:14.157
- The virtual "money "
is soaring once again,

01:14.157 --> 01:16.577
leading to a high-tech gold rush.

01:16.577 --> 01:19.162
- Prospectors are heading west,
where cheap,

01:19.162 --> 01:21.957
filthy electricity beckons the desperate.

01:21.957 --> 01:24.793
- This gives me a desperate idea!

01:24.793 --> 01:26.378
- Haven't you learned that Bitcoin

01:26.378 --> 01:28.672
is just a pyramid scheme for rubes?

01:28.672 --> 01:30.465
- Yes, and my plan

01:30.465 --> 01:33.051
is to exploit those rubes!

01:33.051 --> 01:34.052
[click, beeping]

01:34.052 --> 01:38.015
You see, the new mining chips
are made from element 81,

01:38.015 --> 01:41.393
thallium,
a rare element found out west.

01:41.393 --> 01:43.520
I plan to actually mine it,

01:43.520 --> 01:46.565
then sell it to the Bitcoin "miners."

01:46.565 --> 01:49.401
It's a sure way to repay my loan brokers.

01:49.401 --> 01:50.903
[all gasp]

01:50.903 --> 01:51.945
♪ dramatic sting ♪

01:51.945 --> 01:55.240
- Yo. We're also leg brokers.

01:55.240 --> 01:57.159
- Goodbye, Robot Mafia!

01:57.159 --> 01:59.161
♪

01:59.161 --> 02:00.662
[zooming]

02:00.662 --> 02:01.955
[electricity fizzling]

02:01.955 --> 02:05.918
- The Bitcoin mines are using
such colossal amounts of power

02:05.918 --> 02:08.086
that it's ionizing the atmosphere.

02:08.086 --> 02:11.381
We'll need to land
and drive the rest of the way.

02:11.381 --> 02:13.759
- I'll set her down on the Donner trail.

02:13.759 --> 02:18.096
♪ Wild West-esque music ♪

02:18.096 --> 02:21.141
It's a good thing we brought the oxen.
Usually, we don't.

02:21.141 --> 02:22.768
- I've never been out west before,

02:22.768 --> 02:25.854
but I'm learning a lot from these
Borax Kid action books.

02:25.854 --> 02:27.523
MAXWELL'S DEMON:
I'm robbing this vault

02:27.523 --> 02:30.025
and ain't no ionic compound gonna stop me!

02:30.025 --> 02:31.985
[gun cocks]
BORAX KID: Freeze, Maxwell's Demon.

02:31.985 --> 02:34.530
I'd advise you to drop
those gold molecules.

02:34.530 --> 02:38.450
MAXWELL'S DEMON: The Borax Kid!
I'm gonna pump you full of lead.

02:38.450 --> 02:40.369
[gunshots]

02:40.369 --> 02:43.580
- You know, 'round these parts,
folks don't think things.

02:43.580 --> 02:45.624
They reckon them.
And instead of an idiot,

02:45.624 --> 02:47.459
I'll be known as a galoot!

02:48.085 --> 02:51.547
- Isn't this scenery spectacular, Dwight?
- Uh-huh.

02:51.547 --> 02:54.341
Your mother thought you'd enjoy
some fresh air for once.

02:54.341 --> 02:56.218
[video game beeping]
- She sure was wrong.

02:56.218 --> 02:58.971
- Well, anyway, I'm really looking forward

02:58.971 --> 03:01.431
to some quality father-son time.

03:01.431 --> 03:02.683
- With who?

03:03.559 --> 03:04.768
[video game beeping stops]

03:04.768 --> 03:07.938
♪ grandiose music ♪

03:07.938 --> 03:09.481
- Ah, crypto country.

03:09.481 --> 03:12.109
There's thallium in them thar hills!

03:12.109 --> 03:14.528
Priceless, toxic thallium.

03:16.905 --> 03:18.615
- Um, is this thallium?

03:18.615 --> 03:20.659
[teeth crack]
[smacking lips]

03:20.659 --> 03:23.328
- Oh my, yes! High-grade ore!

03:23.328 --> 03:25.664
- Um, Professor? Toxic.

03:25.664 --> 03:28.166
- Relax. They're my prospecting teeth.

03:28.876 --> 03:29.960
[chattering]

03:29.960 --> 03:32.838
[lisping]: Oh, quit your chattering.
We're almost there.

03:32.838 --> 03:35.757
♪ Western-style music ♪

03:35.757 --> 03:38.343
- Welcome to Doge City!

03:38.343 --> 03:41.889
Looks like you got
seven hornswogglers and a galoot!

03:41.889 --> 03:44.266
♪

03:44.266 --> 03:46.101
- Woo-hoo! We made it!

03:46.101 --> 03:48.437
- It's pretty lawless out here
in crypto country,

03:48.437 --> 03:50.147
so put on your protective headgear.

03:50.147 --> 03:52.274
♪

03:52.274 --> 03:53.358
[video game beeping]

03:54.693 --> 03:55.736
Hiya!

03:55.736 --> 03:58.238
[groaning, grunts]

04:01.658 --> 04:05.662
♪

04:07.331 --> 04:09.333
[horse snorts]
[roadrunner meeps]

04:09.708 --> 04:13.670
- Kind of old-fashioned for a town
built on high-speed computation.

04:13.670 --> 04:16.048
- Well, every watt of electricity

04:16.048 --> 04:18.675
goes to the Bitcoin mining computers.

04:18.675 --> 04:19.843
For everyone else,

04:19.843 --> 04:23.055
it's practically like living
in the Old West.

04:23.055 --> 04:25.057
- Old West. Got it.

04:25.057 --> 04:27.935
- Until we stake our claim
and strike it rich,

04:27.935 --> 04:29.895
keep in mind, we're bankrupt.

04:29.895 --> 04:33.565
So we'll all need to do
Old West stuff to get by.

04:33.565 --> 04:35.526
- Old West. Got it.

04:35.526 --> 04:38.445
♪ saloon tack piano playing ♪

04:38.445 --> 04:40.781
[quiet saloon chatter]

04:46.203 --> 04:48.330
- Welcome, friends. What'll you have?

04:48.330 --> 04:51.041
- Your freest beverage. We're very poor.

04:51.041 --> 04:54.878
- Gotcha. I'll just mix all the unfinished
drinks together and start a tab.

04:55.629 --> 04:58.298
- She seems nice.
- At times, yes.

04:58.298 --> 05:01.301
Though her mood fluctuates
like the price of Bitcoin.

05:02.219 --> 05:03.303
[yells]

05:03.303 --> 05:05.848
- And don't come back
till you settle your tab!

05:05.848 --> 05:08.559
Though, I do regret hurting you.
I tell you what.

05:08.559 --> 05:10.978
Go see the girls in the back room.
It's on me.

05:10.978 --> 05:12.479
- Girls?
- Yep.

05:12.479 --> 05:15.357
Delilah runs a house
of ill repute in back.

05:15.357 --> 05:17.442
- "Ill"? You mean a hospital?

05:17.442 --> 05:18.819
- I mean a cathouse.

05:18.819 --> 05:19.945
- A pet store?

05:19.945 --> 05:20.988
- A brothel.

05:20.988 --> 05:22.447
- A soup kitchen?!

05:22.447 --> 05:24.783
- Yeah. A soup kitchen.

05:24.783 --> 05:26.994
[maniacal laugh]
[gunshots, man yelling]

05:26.994 --> 05:29.997
♪ intimidating Western music ♪

05:30.914 --> 05:32.916
- Whoa! Who's that?

05:32.916 --> 05:35.919
- A psychotic killer, that's who!
Get down!

05:36.461 --> 05:38.672
- Hey, Roberto! What's with the piece?

05:38.672 --> 05:40.382
I thought you were more of a knife guy.

05:40.382 --> 05:42.968
- Out here in the West,
I need something shootier.

05:42.968 --> 05:46.263
Like this gun-knife I invented-stole!

05:46.263 --> 05:48.307
Where's that beer I ordered-didn't order?!

05:48.307 --> 05:51.226
- You didn't order a-- [yelps]

05:51.226 --> 05:54.605
- Say, you're new in town and low on cash.

05:54.605 --> 05:57.941
You interested in a job as a barmaid
and/or a prostitute?

05:57.941 --> 06:01.862
- Um, I'm not sure Leela
has the skills to be a barmaid.

06:01.862 --> 06:03.113
- Gimme the tray!

06:03.822 --> 06:05.699
[horse whinnying]

06:05.699 --> 06:08.368
- Alright, up next, our final item.

06:08.368 --> 06:10.704
This burro is in near-mint condition.

06:10.704 --> 06:14.124
Perfect for hauling Bitcoin,
light housework, or just abusing.

06:14.124 --> 06:15.709
Bidders? Bidders? Do I have any bidders?

06:15.709 --> 06:17.961
- Twelve-millionths of a Bitcoin!

06:17.961 --> 06:20.547
- Twelve micro-Bitcoin.
Do I hear 13? Thirteen, 13?

06:20.547 --> 06:21.965
- Not from me, you don't!

06:21.965 --> 06:24.968
- Fifteen!
I always wanted to own a racehorse.

06:24.968 --> 06:26.512
- That's a donkey, Bender.

06:26.512 --> 06:29.014
- Donkeys are just ugly horses, Amy.

06:29.014 --> 06:31.225
[bell clangs]
- Sold to the zoologist over there!

06:31.225 --> 06:34.019
- Oh! I'm gonna call him Rusty.

06:34.019 --> 06:35.979
- Good 'cause that's his name!

06:35.979 --> 06:37.981
♪

06:37.981 --> 06:40.025
[birds chirping]

06:40.025 --> 06:42.861
- Ah! This looks like
a good place to make camp.

06:42.861 --> 06:45.656
Doesn't it look like
a good place to make camp?

06:45.656 --> 06:48.450
- It looks stupid.
This whole trip is stupid.

06:48.450 --> 06:49.701
You're stupid, Pops!

06:49.701 --> 06:53.121
- I appreciate
your constructive criticism, son.

06:53.121 --> 06:55.082
- I wish Roberto were my dad.

06:55.082 --> 06:58.168
He's cooler than a green snake
smoking a sugar cane vape.

06:58.168 --> 07:00.879
- No self-respecting green snake
would do that!

07:00.879 --> 07:02.089
[imitating Roberto's laugh]

07:02.089 --> 07:05.092
♪ triumphant Western music ♪

07:07.511 --> 07:10.514
[clank]
- Kind sir, could you assay this nugget?

07:10.514 --> 07:14.476
By my tooth test,
I estimate it's 0.3% thallium.

07:14.476 --> 07:18.438
- Tooth test? [cackles]
Balderweeds.

07:18.438 --> 07:21.149
Let's see what
my metallurgical analyzer says.

07:21.650 --> 07:24.152
[chomp, beeping, ding]

07:24.152 --> 07:26.196
ANALYZER:
0.3% thallium.

07:26.196 --> 07:27.739
- Hoo-hoo, boy!

07:27.739 --> 07:30.409
I'll give you 100 micro-Bitcoin for it.

07:30.409 --> 07:33.787
- But weed a million times that amount
or we're gonna get clamped!

07:33.787 --> 07:36.748
- [cackles] Robot Mafia, huh? Eh.

07:36.748 --> 07:40.127
Well, maybe there's some thallium
in that there chassis of yours.

07:40.127 --> 07:41.837
[whirring, clanking]

07:41.837 --> 07:44.089
- Assay my shiny metal ass!

07:44.673 --> 07:45.841
[chomps]
[yelps]

07:45.841 --> 07:47.092
[beeping, buzz]

07:47.092 --> 07:50.888
ANALYZER:
0.0000...

07:50.888 --> 07:53.015
- Tain't even worth melting down.

07:53.015 --> 07:55.767
- Well then,
perhaps my ass might be of value to you

07:55.767 --> 07:57.144
in some other way?

07:57.144 --> 07:59.938
- Eh, it might make a good frying pan,

07:59.938 --> 08:02.566
but fried food makes me cackle. [cackles]

08:02.566 --> 08:04.401
- We'll just sell you the nugget.

08:04.943 --> 08:06.570
[whoosh]
[cash register dings]

08:06.570 --> 08:10.574
May I ask who turns
the thallium into microchips?

08:10.574 --> 08:12.576
- I'm an all-in-one operation.

08:12.576 --> 08:15.662
My motto is,
"He who smelts it, dealts it!"

08:15.662 --> 08:17.456
[clattering]
[beeping, squish]

08:21.168 --> 08:22.211
[ding]

08:22.961 --> 08:25.881
Pop one of those in a high-end server,
and blam!

08:25.881 --> 08:28.383
You're mining crypto.
[ding]

08:28.383 --> 08:31.386
Ooh, lookie there! Found another Bitcoin!

08:31.386 --> 08:33.430
[beep]
Aw, dog dumplings.

08:33.430 --> 08:35.265
It's just a danged Ethereum.

08:35.265 --> 08:37.935
♪

08:37.935 --> 08:39.228
[door creaks]

08:39.228 --> 08:40.896
- Hello, I'm Zoidberg.

08:40.896 --> 08:42.773
Like you, I'm a doctor.

08:42.773 --> 08:45.526
So, uh, what's your survival rate?

08:45.526 --> 08:47.819
- Pretty high. I'm a psychiatrist.

08:47.819 --> 08:50.531
Got a patient coming 'round
for anger management about now.

08:50.531 --> 08:51.532
[door opens]

08:51.532 --> 08:55.118
- Hiya, Doc.
Boy, it's been a stressful week.

08:55.118 --> 08:57.037
What's with the jumbo prawn?

08:57.037 --> 08:59.289
- A colleague. Mind if he sits in?

08:59.289 --> 09:00.958
- Yes, I do mind!

09:00.958 --> 09:04.086
I value doctor-patient confidentiality!

09:04.086 --> 09:05.921
[screaming]

09:05.921 --> 09:07.840
Patang!
DOCTOR: Ah!

09:07.840 --> 09:08.882
[thud]

09:16.181 --> 09:19.184
♪ saloon tack piano playing ♪

09:19.184 --> 09:20.519
- So, how's business?

09:20.519 --> 09:23.397
- Disappointing.
I only got 30 cents in tips

09:23.397 --> 09:25.691
and one request to visit the back room.

09:25.691 --> 09:28.777
I mean, I wouldn't go,
but it's nice to be asked.

09:28.777 --> 09:31.446
Can you think of anything
I can do to look sluttier?

09:31.446 --> 09:33.448
- Nope. [gasps]

09:33.448 --> 09:35.117
Look! The Borax Kid!

09:35.117 --> 09:37.035
And his sidekick Mumbles!

09:37.035 --> 09:40.038
- You know he's not actually a hero
like in his books, right?

09:40.038 --> 09:43.000
He's a poker cheat
and a low-down base mineral.

09:43.000 --> 09:45.836
- Wow. The Borax Kid.

09:45.836 --> 09:47.713
Excuse me, Mr. Kid.

09:47.713 --> 09:51.300
My name is Fry, and I'm a big fan
of your young adult adventures.

09:51.300 --> 09:53.594
- Oh, really? Uh, do you play poker?

09:53.594 --> 09:56.013
- Yeah, but I was warned
not to play poker with you.

09:56.013 --> 09:58.265
- Well, then how about a hand
of Colorado Chump?

09:58.265 --> 09:59.766
- As long as it's not poker.

10:02.144 --> 10:03.562
So what are you doing here?

10:03.562 --> 10:05.981
Fighting evil or just helping townspeople?

10:05.981 --> 10:07.816
- Not much money in helping folks.

10:08.525 --> 10:10.694
Double chump. You lose.

10:10.694 --> 10:13.488
ROBERTO:
I heard the Borax Kid's in town.

10:13.488 --> 10:15.240
Come on out here, Kid!

10:15.240 --> 10:17.534
- Mumbles, go see
what all that fuss is about.

10:17.534 --> 10:19.953
And wear my signature hat.

10:19.953 --> 10:22.247
[mumbling]

10:23.373 --> 10:24.875
[gunshots]
ROBERTO: Pa-pow-pow!

10:29.171 --> 10:30.964
- Mumbles is dead!

10:30.964 --> 10:32.716
[mumbling]

10:32.716 --> 10:36.053
Don't argue with me, Mumbles.
I'm the town doctor.

10:36.053 --> 10:39.723
- Well, shucks. My sidekicks
seem to be dying right regular.

10:39.723 --> 10:41.642
And in gruesome fashion.

10:41.642 --> 10:43.143
Care to be my new sidekick?

10:43.143 --> 10:45.896
- Really?
Do I get to die in your next book?

10:45.896 --> 10:46.980
- Page three.

10:46.980 --> 10:49.107
- Then you got yourself a galoot.

10:50.108 --> 10:53.362
♪

10:53.362 --> 10:55.864
- Nice camp. Is this my tent?

10:55.864 --> 10:57.866
- No. You only come in to tidy up.

10:57.866 --> 11:01.203
There's just enough room for me
and my private library there.

11:01.203 --> 11:02.871
- Can I sleep in the library?

11:02.871 --> 11:05.749
- I'd like to say yes,
but then it wouldn't be private.

11:07.334 --> 11:09.336
♪

11:09.336 --> 11:11.255
- This place has too much outdoors!

11:11.255 --> 11:13.257
It's all bugs and no Wi-Fi.

11:13.257 --> 11:15.384
- Don't get your dreads in a knot, son.

11:15.384 --> 11:16.844
Any more than they're supposed to be.

11:16.844 --> 11:19.263
How about a father-son limbo break?

11:19.263 --> 11:21.974
- I hate limbo, Dad! Limbo is stupid.

11:22.808 --> 11:26.186
- Limbo stupid? Where did I go wrong?

11:26.186 --> 11:28.313
- Probably when you took up limbo.

11:28.313 --> 11:30.816
From what I'm hearing, it's stupid.

11:30.816 --> 11:34.194
- Bender! Where are the shovels
I asked you to pack?

11:34.194 --> 11:35.696
- Oh, you said shovels?

11:35.696 --> 11:37.948
I thought you said
take a break and do nothing.

11:37.948 --> 11:40.659
- Hm.
Then we'll just have to find thallium

11:40.659 --> 11:43.704
the old-fashioned way. By panning.

11:43.704 --> 11:45.372
- Panning? With what?

11:48.834 --> 11:51.753
- [sighs] Sometimes,
I think a detachable ass

11:51.753 --> 11:54.965
is more a curse than a blessing.
Come on, Rusty.

11:54.965 --> 11:56.967
[clopping]

11:56.967 --> 12:00.220
♪

12:00.220 --> 12:02.222
♪ We're just a guy with no ass ♪

12:02.222 --> 12:04.516
♪ And his ass ♪

12:04.516 --> 12:08.437
♪ Assin' it up under an asinine sky ♪

12:08.437 --> 12:12.399
♪ Assin' to the tumbleweeds
as we ass by ♪

12:12.399 --> 12:14.526
♪ Yodeling a cowboy tune ♪

12:14.526 --> 12:15.861
♪ But, not yet! ♪

12:15.861 --> 12:19.615
♪ People sass me
on my ass as we pass ♪

12:19.615 --> 12:23.535
♪ They say, wouldn't it be better
if my ass rode me? ♪

12:23.535 --> 12:25.829
♪ They tell me I outweigh my ass ♪

12:25.829 --> 12:27.748
♪ By a factor of three ♪

12:27.748 --> 12:30.042
♪ So, I punch 'em and I kick their ♪

12:30.042 --> 12:32.586
♪ Yodel-odel-ay-hee-hoo ♪

12:32.586 --> 12:36.048
♪ harmonizing braying ♪

12:36.048 --> 12:38.425
♪ Ass, butt, rear-end, ass ♪

12:38.425 --> 12:39.968
♪ Yodel-ay hee hoo-- ♪

12:39.968 --> 12:41.553
[bones crack]
[yelps]

12:41.553 --> 12:44.056
What the? Rusty! No!
[mournful bray]

12:44.056 --> 12:46.308
[both screaming]
[crash]

12:46.308 --> 12:49.811
Oh, why didn't I listen to my own song?!

12:49.811 --> 12:52.814
[playing tack piano, rollers rattling]

12:55.234 --> 12:58.987
- Get yourself tuned or get outta town,
you overgrowed teletype machine.

12:58.987 --> 13:00.822
[cackling]

13:00.822 --> 13:02.908
- Eh, shut your cackling trap!

13:02.908 --> 13:04.493
[cackling]
[clanging]

13:04.493 --> 13:05.994
- Cram that racket!

13:05.994 --> 13:08.789
This is a nice, quiet saloon
with attached bordello.

13:10.499 --> 13:12.960
- You handle the menfolk pretty well.

13:12.960 --> 13:14.670
But mess with my customers again,

13:14.670 --> 13:16.672
and I'll kill you in your sleep!

13:16.672 --> 13:18.131
Lovin' the boots.

13:18.131 --> 13:20.634
- Um, have you considered seeing someone

13:20.634 --> 13:23.011
about your mood swings?
- No!

13:23.011 --> 13:24.555
But it is a good idea.

13:28.517 --> 13:30.018
[doors open]
DWIGHT: Mr. Roberto?

13:30.018 --> 13:32.396
Folks call me Amarillo Dwight.

13:32.396 --> 13:35.399
On account of I wrote
a geography report on it.

13:35.399 --> 13:37.025
Done got me a "A."

13:37.025 --> 13:40.279
How's about you and me
team up and rob stuff?

13:40.279 --> 13:42.614
- What are you, like, 11?
- Twelve.

13:42.614 --> 13:45.617
- Close enough.
I need a kid for a job I'm planning.

13:45.617 --> 13:47.119
See that stagecoach?

13:47.119 --> 13:48.203
[horses neigh]

13:48.203 --> 13:49.663
It's taking a USB stick

13:49.663 --> 13:52.291
with a company's weekly haul
of Bitcoin credentials

13:52.291 --> 13:54.459
to a bank in San Francisc-y.

13:54.459 --> 13:57.796
Only, they ain't never gonna
reach San Francisc-y.

13:57.796 --> 14:00.716
- Why not? They using Apple Maps?

14:00.716 --> 14:03.719
♪

14:04.720 --> 14:07.347
- [groans] Not one patient.

14:07.347 --> 14:10.767
Not even a case of splinters
to treat with my bone saw.

14:11.768 --> 14:13.270
[weak bray]

14:13.270 --> 14:16.273
Thanks, robot, but I couldn't
eat a thing right now.

14:16.273 --> 14:18.567
[weak braying]

14:18.567 --> 14:20.944
- [sniffles] Can you save him, Doc?

14:20.944 --> 14:24.072
- If it's something that
can be cured by a bone saw!

14:26.200 --> 14:27.743
I'll need anesthetic!

14:27.743 --> 14:29.995
Get me a bottle of animal whiskey!

14:29.995 --> 14:30.996
ROBERTO:
Ha-ha!

14:31.622 --> 14:33.665
They see a cute kid lying in the road,

14:33.665 --> 14:35.501
stagecoach gotta stop.

14:35.501 --> 14:37.586
Then I jump out and stab 'em!

14:37.586 --> 14:38.504
Bang!

14:38.504 --> 14:41.215
- But, won't that be, like, murder?

14:41.215 --> 14:43.383
'Cause colleges look at stuff like that.

14:43.383 --> 14:45.385
- Here they come!
Shut up and look cute.

14:45.385 --> 14:48.388
[horses trotting]

14:51.892 --> 14:53.310
[Dwight screams]

14:54.478 --> 14:56.480
Guess you ain't as cute as I thought.

14:56.480 --> 14:57.731
[groaning]

14:58.190 --> 14:59.399
[snaps, yelps]

14:59.399 --> 15:02.402
♪

15:02.402 --> 15:04.738
[mechanism whirring]

15:04.738 --> 15:07.241
- The West can be dangerous
at night, Leela,

15:07.241 --> 15:09.159
so thanks for walking me home.

15:09.159 --> 15:11.703
[roaring]
[yelping]

15:11.703 --> 15:14.748
Don't worry. The Kid will save us, right?
BORAX KID: Right.

15:16.041 --> 15:17.042
[whimpering]

15:17.042 --> 15:18.544
- Better back off, puma.
[snarls]

15:18.544 --> 15:20.462
- I think it's actually a cougar.

15:20.462 --> 15:23.340
- Puma, cougar, whatever! Get him, Kid!

15:23.340 --> 15:25.551
- Or a mountain lion. You know,
they're really all the same animal.

15:25.551 --> 15:26.927
[roaring]
[screams]

15:28.220 --> 15:31.223
[frightened growling, snarling]

15:31.849 --> 15:32.850
[cocks gun]

15:32.850 --> 15:35.018
- It seems I bravely shot that catamount

15:35.018 --> 15:37.145
just in time after Fry missed.

15:37.145 --> 15:39.898
- Thanks, Kid.
Maybe I was wrong about you.

15:39.898 --> 15:43.026
- Beautiful ladies are wrong
about lots of things.

15:43.026 --> 15:44.945
[clicks tongue]
[Leela giggles]

15:44.945 --> 15:48.073
- Ah, it's nice to see you two
getting along so intimately.

15:48.073 --> 15:49.825
♪

15:49.825 --> 15:51.535
- It's hopeless!

15:51.535 --> 15:53.370
There's barely any thallium!

15:53.370 --> 15:55.747
Just worthless gold.

15:55.747 --> 15:58.000
- Well, Rusty's good as new!

15:58.000 --> 16:00.711
- I performed surgery on Bender's ass!

16:00.711 --> 16:02.629
Zoidberg is the hero!

16:02.629 --> 16:03.672
[loud clang]

16:03.672 --> 16:06.008
- No! Bender's ass is!

16:06.008 --> 16:07.759
♪

16:07.759 --> 16:09.094
- I mean his butt ass.

16:09.094 --> 16:10.470
♪

16:10.470 --> 16:11.680
[all gasping]

16:12.347 --> 16:14.141
- It's so beautiful.

16:14.141 --> 16:15.934
Hey, what's that big rock on it?

16:15.934 --> 16:19.229
- It's enough thallium
to pay off all our debts!

16:19.229 --> 16:21.398
Eh, well, mine, anyway.

16:21.398 --> 16:24.109
- Only the assay shop's
closed for the night,

16:24.109 --> 16:25.777
and it's getting dark.

16:25.777 --> 16:27.988
- We'll have to take turns
guarding the nugget

16:27.988 --> 16:29.907
with our lives until morning.

16:29.907 --> 16:31.533
I'd take a shift myself,

16:31.533 --> 16:33.702
but I am already in my pajamas.

16:34.453 --> 16:36.455
[snoring]

16:36.455 --> 16:39.458
♪

16:39.458 --> 16:43.045
- I steal it. I steal it not.
I steal it...

16:43.045 --> 16:44.046
[gun cocks]
[yelps]

16:44.046 --> 16:45.422
- Gimme the nugget!

16:45.422 --> 16:48.300
And the daisy, too.
I gotta know how it comes out!

16:48.300 --> 16:51.303
[birds chirping]

16:52.221 --> 16:54.473
[all yawning]

16:54.473 --> 16:56.141
- Ah, nature.

16:56.141 --> 17:00.062
I hate it. Let's sell that thallium nugget
and hit the trail.

17:00.062 --> 17:02.105
- Oh, no. The nugget is gone!

17:02.105 --> 17:03.982
And so is Bender.

17:03.982 --> 17:06.068
[muffled braying]
- Eh, wha?

17:06.068 --> 17:08.445
AMY:
Oh, my gosh! Rusty!

17:08.445 --> 17:10.697
Bray us what happened!

17:10.697 --> 17:13.909
[braying]

17:13.909 --> 17:16.620
Come on! He's picked up Bender's scent!

17:16.620 --> 17:17.913
- His what now?

17:17.913 --> 17:20.832
♪ saloon tack piano playing ♪

17:21.667 --> 17:22.668
♪ music stops ♪

17:23.961 --> 17:27.756
♪ tense music ♪

17:28.257 --> 17:29.925
[braying]

17:29.925 --> 17:32.344
- Back room don't open
till church lets out.

17:33.971 --> 17:35.430
- [gasps] It's empty!

17:36.139 --> 17:38.684
- This is the worst brothel
I've ever seen.

17:38.684 --> 17:41.103
♪ music builds ♪

17:41.103 --> 17:43.981
[gasps]
[beeping]

17:43.981 --> 17:46.942
- It's an immense Bitcoin mine!

17:46.942 --> 17:48.902
Or an even worse brothel.

17:48.902 --> 17:51.905
- These aren't servers.
They're robot heads!

17:51.905 --> 17:54.491
Someone's using them to mine Bitcoin!

17:54.491 --> 17:57.703
- That's actually a pretty reasonable
use case for robot heads. But--

17:57.703 --> 17:59.580
- Hey! It's a guy I know.

17:59.580 --> 18:00.664
[all gasping]

18:00.664 --> 18:02.165
Are you okay, Bender?

18:02.165 --> 18:05.169
- No, I'm not okay!
That's a stupid question!

18:05.169 --> 18:07.671
- I was peacefully stealing your thallium,

18:07.671 --> 18:09.381
when, suddenly-- Ha-ha!

18:09.381 --> 18:12.092
I was kidnapped
by our friend from the saloon.

18:12.092 --> 18:15.012
[door opens]
- I'm not your friend.

18:15.012 --> 18:17.181
♪ dramatic sting ♪

18:17.181 --> 18:19.349
[laughs] Though, I do like you a lot.

18:20.350 --> 18:23.604
♪ dramatic music ♪

18:23.604 --> 18:26.023
- Didn't you ever wonder
who was gettin' rich

18:26.023 --> 18:28.275
off all this Bitcoin nonsense?

18:28.275 --> 18:30.986
- Never!
- Computer servers are expensive,

18:30.986 --> 18:33.780
but robot heads are cheap. Heck, free.

18:33.780 --> 18:36.992
- Mining Bitcoin
with kidnapped robot heads?

18:36.992 --> 18:39.036
It's pure evil!

18:39.036 --> 18:43.081
- Hardly. I donate all the proceeds
to a local orphanage.

18:43.081 --> 18:44.666
ALL:
Aw...

18:44.666 --> 18:48.295
- But I can't let you tell anyone
about my generous scheme,

18:48.295 --> 18:49.796
so I'll have to seal you

18:49.796 --> 18:52.341
in this comfortably
air-conditioned warehouse.

18:52.341 --> 18:54.301
Forever!
[all gasp]

18:54.301 --> 18:56.053
But I'll drop by every day with snacks.

18:56.053 --> 18:58.222
HERMES: Aw...
ZOIDBERG: Snacks are good.

18:58.555 --> 19:00.057
[beep, slam]

19:00.057 --> 19:03.060
[humming]

19:05.896 --> 19:06.897
[stops humming]

19:06.897 --> 19:08.398
♪

19:08.398 --> 19:09.816
♪ dramatic sting ♪

19:09.816 --> 19:10.817
- Huh.

19:12.486 --> 19:14.571
- Crypto mining was total hell.

19:14.571 --> 19:16.156
Any number you can think of,

19:16.156 --> 19:18.700
there's a number bigger than that!
[banging]

19:18.700 --> 19:20.702
- So how do we get out of here?

19:20.702 --> 19:22.621
- Easy. We'll burrow out!

19:22.621 --> 19:24.873
[braying]

19:24.873 --> 19:26.458
Burrow! Burrow!

19:28.710 --> 19:30.087
[weakly]:
I deserved that.

19:30.087 --> 19:32.673
♪

19:32.673 --> 19:34.925
- This tie pin? Why, it was a gift

19:34.925 --> 19:37.469
from my good friend Diamond Jim Diamond.

19:37.469 --> 19:40.514
- That guy who's just a big diamond?
You know him?

19:40.514 --> 19:42.683
- Step away from Leela, Kid.

19:42.683 --> 19:43.684
♪

19:43.684 --> 19:46.520
The jig is up! I found your collection

19:46.520 --> 19:47.855
of Buffalo Bill Cobalt novels.

19:47.855 --> 19:50.774
You just copied those
and replaced his name with yours!

19:50.774 --> 19:52.192
- What?!
- Well, now,

19:52.192 --> 19:53.777
there's nothing illegal about that.

19:53.777 --> 19:56.196
Those old stories are public domain.

19:56.196 --> 19:59.366
I change up a few words
and claim the copyright for myself.

19:59.366 --> 20:02.494
Ya ever heard of Cinderella?
- That is so evil!

20:02.494 --> 20:04.705
- I'm calling you out, Kid.

20:04.705 --> 20:08.292
♪ dramatic music ♪

20:08.750 --> 20:11.628
♪ dramatic tack piano ♪

20:11.628 --> 20:15.132
- I told you, stop that racket! [cackling]

20:15.132 --> 20:17.801
- Not till you stop that damn cackling!

20:17.801 --> 20:19.720
- Then I'm callin' you out.

20:19.720 --> 20:21.305
[cackling]

20:28.812 --> 20:31.106
[rumbling, crumbling]

20:31.106 --> 20:32.816
[Rusty braying]

20:32.816 --> 20:34.776
BENDER:
Delilah, you head-napper!

20:34.776 --> 20:36.528
I'm calling you out!

20:36.528 --> 20:38.697
- You're on.
[cackling continues]

20:38.697 --> 20:41.450
♪

20:45.078 --> 20:47.247
- Look out, Fry!
He's got the ace of spades!

20:49.583 --> 20:52.085
- That, sir, was my cheatin' hand.

20:53.378 --> 20:55.297
[gunfire]

21:00.886 --> 21:01.887
[cackling]

21:02.387 --> 21:05.390
♪ faster tack piano ♪

21:07.392 --> 21:09.102
[Hermes screaming]

21:09.102 --> 21:11.188
- Pops! Get outta there!

21:11.188 --> 21:14.691
- I'm too scared!
There's bullets in every dimension!

21:14.691 --> 21:15.776
[whirring]

21:15.776 --> 21:17.736
- Hang on! I'm limboing in!

21:17.736 --> 21:19.780
- You. Play something Jamaican.
[flips coin]

21:21.114 --> 21:23.784
♪ Jamaican music ♪

21:24.451 --> 21:27.579
[gunfire, cackling continue]

21:31.917 --> 21:34.920
[cackling continues]
[shoes popping]

21:40.759 --> 21:41.760
[spine cracking]

21:41.760 --> 21:43.178
- Your spine!

21:43.178 --> 21:44.930
It's magnificent!

21:44.930 --> 21:46.807
- I take after my dad.

21:46.807 --> 21:48.892
Also, I got run over. Now, follow me!

21:48.892 --> 21:52.563
[shoes popping]

21:52.563 --> 21:53.981
[yelps]

21:54.398 --> 21:55.649
[bullet ricochets]
[piano stops]

21:55.649 --> 21:58.986
[gunfire continues]

22:00.529 --> 22:03.240
- This gun violence has to end!

22:03.240 --> 22:05.784
Can't we all just agree to use knives?

22:05.784 --> 22:07.035
[gunfire stops]
Ha-ha!

22:07.035 --> 22:09.037
- Well, shucks.

22:13.083 --> 22:14.209
- Ow!

22:14.209 --> 22:15.919
- Oops. Sorry, Leela.

22:15.919 --> 22:19.298
- Ma'am, I'd be right honored
to disinfect your wound

22:19.298 --> 22:21.717
with the kiss of borax.

22:22.759 --> 22:25.554
May I escort you to the brothel,
so as you can lie down?

22:25.554 --> 22:28.765
- I've never been so offended
yet slightly flattered!

22:28.765 --> 22:30.601
- Then, I reckon I'll be moseying off

22:30.601 --> 22:33.103
to plagiarize another adventure. Ma'am.

22:36.440 --> 22:39.610
- Perhaps I could disinfect your wound.

22:39.610 --> 22:42.696
- I'd like that.
Care to escort me to the brothel?

22:44.865 --> 22:49.411
- It seems, Miss Delilah,
you've taken a shot to the bustle.

22:49.411 --> 22:53.040
- Fortunately, it bounced off
your damned thallium nugget.

22:53.040 --> 22:55.042
Here. It's rightfully yours.

22:55.042 --> 22:56.460
[bones crack]
PROFESSOR: Oh!

22:56.960 --> 22:59.046
Well, I'd better go exchange this

22:59.046 --> 23:00.672
for Bitcoin, so I can--

23:00.672 --> 23:02.591
- Pay back the Robot Mafia?!
[clamping]

23:02.591 --> 23:05.594
- Exactly. I'll be back in a moment.

23:08.889 --> 23:10.182
- And in the meantime,

23:10.182 --> 23:13.185
how would you gents fancy
a visit to the back room?

23:13.185 --> 23:15.812
DONBOT: That sounds like something
we would enjoy.

23:15.812 --> 23:17.898
[panting]

23:17.898 --> 23:19.525
- I love you, Pops.

23:19.525 --> 23:21.735
And limbo is not entirely stupid.

23:21.735 --> 23:24.446
- Oh, son. Neither are you.

23:24.446 --> 23:26.448
♪ heartwarming music ♪

23:26.448 --> 23:28.659
♪ dramatic crescendo ♪

23:28.659 --> 23:30.452
- If we ever get outta here,

23:30.452 --> 23:33.997
I'm gonna give this brothel
a really bad Yelp review.

23:33.997 --> 23:35.499
♪ dramatic sting ♪

23:37.042 --> 23:40.045
♪
